0.1.23.creator: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.23.description: IterativeSinCluster is an additive synthesizer. This synth computes 512 sine waves for each note to make tone cluster. I somehow thought "iterative sin" is a valid term. Correct term is "recursive sine".

0.1.22.name: TrapezoidSynth
0.1.22.creator: Takamitsu Endo
0.1.22.description: TrapezoidSynth is a monophonic synthesizer equipped with 2 trapezoid oscillator. Trapezoid oscillator is based on PTR (Polynomial Transition Regions) and it has a drawback that increasing noise at high frequency. Therefore 8 times oversampled. 2 pitch shifters are added to make some chord.

0.2.15.name: FDNCymbal
0.2.15.creator: Takamitsu Endo
0.2.15.description: FDNCymbal is a cymbal sound synthesizer. It can also be used as an effect. Unlike the name, most of metallic texture comes from Schroeder allpass section rather than FDN (feedback delay network). FDN section makes nice impact sound when `FDN.Time` is short. Tremolo is added to simulate wobbling of cymbal.

1.0.0.name: Mverb

The OB-Xd was designed to sound as good and as rich as the original. It implements micro random detuning which is a big part of that sound.
